    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 9800 SERIES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s11011" svcsectype="prodspec" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5231" date="03/01/1996">
        <title>CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 9800 SERIES</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9800</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>GENERAL</title>
                <para>The clutch control linkage (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101101">Figure 1</hotlnk>) consists of a suspended clutch pedal connected by a rod
                    to a relay (bellcrank) which is, in turn, connected by another rod to the clutch release shaft
                    lever.
                </para>
                <para>Adjustments are provided to establish correct initial settings and to compensate for wear of
                    clutch disc facings.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1101101" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1101101" filename="../figg11/g1101101.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Clutch Control Linkage</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. PEDAL SHAFT LEVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. PEDAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. RELEASE SHAFT LEVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. LOWER CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. RELAY (BELLCRANK)</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. CAB HINGE BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. RETURN SPRING</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. UPPER CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
    </svcsection>
